  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stabilization Support in Fragile Areas of Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will provide rapid stabilization and early recovery support in target urban and peri-urban areas in Somalia. It is intended to serve as a bridge between more immediate responses in areas impacted by conflict, extremism and also displacement and longer-term development interventions. The project entails sequenced interventions that look at simultaneously building the capacity of caretaker administrators in the target localities, facilitating inclusive community processes, and generating information and context analysis to support community engagement processes, inform government stakeholders and facilitate adaptive programme management.</narrative>
  </description>
